Slackware Current Repository by Conraid

======================================================================

rt-tests (suite of real-time tests)

A set of utilities to test Linux real-time properties.
Includes:
- cyclictest: measures high resolution timer latency
- hackbench: scheduler stress test
- hwlatdetect: finds hardware-induced latencies
- pip_stress: priority inheritance stress test

HOME: https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/utils/rt-tests/rt-tests.git/

======================================================================
NOTE: 

The 'hwlatdetect' utility requires the kernel to be compiled
with CONFIG_HWLAT_TRACER=y. If this option is not set in your
current kernel, hwlatdetect will fail with a "DetectorNotAvailable"
error. Other tools like 'cyclictest' will work regardless of this
setting.

======================
REQUIRES: numactl 

